This article is a presidential proclamation by Barack Obama, honoring the victims of the terrorist attack in Paris, France that occurred on November 13, 2015. The proclamation expresses solidarity with the people of France and condemns the attack as an assault on humanity and universal values. The United States and its allies are committed to bringing the perpetrators to justice and combating terrorism. As a mark of respect, the flag of the United States will be flown at half-staff at various locations until November 19, 2015.